Done. Both `transcript.json` (10 iterations, 40 hypotheses, 40 analyses, schema-validated) and `analysis_summary.txt` are written in the working directory.

**Key findings**

Pembrolizumab program (the dominant signal):
- **Pembro × PD-L1 TPS**: coef +0.60 (p=1.6e-7); benefit confined to PD-L1≥0.5 (20.9% vs 15.6%, p=8e-13)
- **Pembro × TMB-high**: coef +0.17 (p=9e-4)
- **Pembro × STK11**: coef -0.20 (p=0.003); STK11 mutation abolishes the PD-L1-driven pembro benefit
- Pembro benefit is concentrated in current/former smokers and (more so than) females

Prognostic features (all independently significant in MV model): ECOG (-0.38, p=1e-95), stage IV (-0.30), brain mets (-0.26), weight loss (-0.04/%), albumin (+0.09), CRP (-0.005), sex female (+0.08).

Surprising nulls:
- Osimertinib × EGFR (p=0.87), sotorasib × KRAS G12C (p=0.43), and olaparib × BRCA2 (p=0.35) are all null in their matched biomarker subgroups
- LDH, NLR, all 23 SNPs (0/23 Bonferroni-significant), comorbidities, prior therapies, and most SDOH variables are null
